Starting Environment:

Laptop (Linux)
  Minikube
  Kubeadm

Physical Servers
Cloud Servers

For Production Purposes:

Turnkey Solutions
  Provision the necessary VMs and use tools or scripts to configure Kubernetes clusters.
  Responsible for maintaining and patching VMs.
  VM provisioning and configuration handled by you.
  Use scripts for cluster deployment.
  Self-manage VMs, e.g., Kubernetes on AWS using Kops.

Hosted Solutions (Managed Solutions)
  These resemble Kubernetes-as-a-Service offerings.
  Provision VMs.
  Install Kubernetes.
  Manage VM maintenance.
  Examples include Google Kubernetes Engine (GKE).
